We need to compute per Country-Region: count of resellers, count of distinct business types, count of distinct state-province. Use Reseller table. Group by Country-Region. Output columns: Country-Region, reseller_count, business_type_count, state_count. Sort by reseller_count desc.

SQL: SELECT 'Country-Region' AS Country-Region, COUNT(*) AS reseller_count, COUNT(DISTINCT Business Type) AS business_type_count, COUNT(DISTINCT State-Province) AS state_count FROM Reseller GROUP BY Country-Region ORDER BY reseller_count DESC;

But need to quote field names: 'Country-Region', 'Business Type', 'State-Province'. Use double quotes? In DuckDB, identifiers with spaces need quotes. Use "Country-Region", "Business Type", "State-Province". Also column names: reseller_count etc.

SQL: SELECT "Country-Region", COUNT(*) AS reseller_count, COUNT(DISTINCT "Business Type") AS business_type_count, COUNT(DISTINCT "State-Province") AS state_count FROM Reseller GROUP BY "Country-Region" ORDER BY reseller_count DESC;

